The Mayor of the Ditsobotla Municipality in the North West Daniel Buthelezi has been freed after an eight-hour hostage drama.This comes after a group of 32 disgruntled residents, armed with weapons and petrol bombs stormed the municipal offices in Lichtenburg late on Wednesday and held Mayor Buthelezi hostage.Part of the municipality offices has been set alight. Reports say the fire was started by the residents who stormed the council chambers apparently demanding better service delivery. It is reported the building was torched from inside.North West police spokesperson Colonel Sabata Mokgwabone said they are negotiating the release of the mayor. We are currently at the scene. We have our negotiators trying to negotiate with those who are holding the mayor hostage, said Mokgwabone-TNA Reporter 